claim.claim-text:
1. A foldable device frame, comprising:
a front wheel;
left and right side laterally spaced-apart front wheel supports, each of the left and right side front wheel supports having a forward end portion and a rearward end portion, the front wheel being mounted to the forward end portion of at least one of the front wheel supports, the left and right side front wheel supports being rotatable as a unit;
left and right rear wheels;
left and right side laterally spaced-apart rear wheel supports, each of the left and right side rear wheel supports having a lower end portion and an upper end portion, the lower end portions being coupled to at least one of the left and right rear wheels;
left and right side laterally spaced-apart handle members, each of the left and right side handle members having a forward end portion and a rearward end portion, the left and right side handle members being rotatable as a unit, at least one of the left and right side handle members having a handle portion; and
left and right side laterally spaced-apart folding assemblies, each of the left and right side folding assemblies having a first rotatable member and a second rotatable member with each rotatably coupled to a pivot member supported by the upper end portion of a corresponding one of the left and right side rear wheel supports for rotation about a common axis of rotation, the rearward end portion of a corresponding one of the left and right side front wheel supports being fixedly attached to the first rotatable member, and the forward end portion of a corresponding one of the left and right side handle members being fixedly attached to the second rotatable member, wherein the left and right folding assemblies each further include a member slidably movable relative to the corresponding one of the left and right side rear wheel supports, and the first and second rotatable members of each folding assembly further include a notch to receive the member therein when the first and second rotatable members are rotated about the pivot member to position the handle member and the front wheel support attached thereto in an unfolded state.

8. A foldable device for use with at least one front wheel and at least one rear wheel, comprising:
left and right side laterally spaced-apart front wheel supports, each of the left and right side front wheel supports having an end portion, the front wheel supports being configured for mounting of the at least one front wheel thereto, the left and right side front wheel supports being rotatable as a unit;
left and right side laterally spaced-apart rear wheel supports, each of the left and right side rear wheel supports having an end portion, the rear wheel supports being configured for mounting of the at least one rear wheel thereto, the left and right side rear wheel supports being rotatable as a unit;
left and right side laterally spaced-apart handle members, each of the left and right side handle members having an end portion, the left and right side handle members being rotatable as a unit, at least one of the left and right side handle members having a handle portion; and
left and right side laterally spaced-apart folding assemblies, each of the left and right side folding assemblies having a first rotatable member and a second rotatable member with each rotatably coupled to a pivot member, the pivot member being supported by the end portion of one of the front wheel support, rear wheel support and handle member of a corresponding side for rotation about a common axis of rotation, the end portion of a different one of the front wheel support, rear wheel support and handle member of the corresponding side being attached to the first rotatable member for movement therewith and the end portion of another different one of the front wheel support, rear wheel support and handle member of the corresponding side being attached to the second rotatable member for movement therewith, wherein the left and right folding assemblies each further include a movable member, and the first and second rotatable members of each folding assembly each further include a notch to receive the movable member therein when the first and second rotatable members are rotated about the pivot member to position the handle member, the front wheel support and the rear wheel support in an unfolded state.

10. A foldable device for use with at least one front wheel and at least one rear wheel, comprising:
left and right side laterally spaced-apart first members, each of the first members having a first end portion and a second end portion;
left and right side laterally spaced-apart second members, each of the second members having a first end portion and a second end portion;
left and right side laterally spaced-apart third members, each of the third members having a first end portion and a second end portion, at least one of the first end portions of the first members having a mounting portion configured for mounting of the at least one front wheel thereto, at least one of the first end portions of the second members having a mounting portion configured for mounting of the at least one rear wheel thereto, and at least one of the first end portions of the third members having a handle portion; and
left and right side laterally spaced-apart folding assemblies, each of the left and right side folding assemblies having a first rotatable member and a second rotatable member with each rotatably mounted on a pivot member to pivot about the pivot member as a common axis, the second end portion of a first one of the first, second and third members of a corresponding side being attached to the first rotatable member for movement therewith, the second end portion of a different second one of the first, second and third members of the corresponding side being attached to the second rotatable member for movement therewith, and the second end portion of another different third one of the first, second and third members of the corresponding side supporting the pivot member, wherein the left and right folding assemblies each further include a movable member, and the first and second rotatable members of each folding assembly each further include a notch to receive the movable member therein when the first and second rotatable members are rotated about the pivot member to position the handle member, the front wheel support and the rear wheel support in an unfolded state.
